    <item>
      <title>Introduction to Networking — Basics for Beginners</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/post/networking-basics/</link>
      <pubDate>Tue, 16 Jun 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/post/networking-basics/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h2 class=&#34;relative group&#34;&gt;What is a Network?&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;div id=&#34;what-is-a-network&#34; class=&#34;anchor&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &#xD;&#xA;    &lt;span&#xD;&#xA;        class=&#34;absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 -start-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100 select-none&#34;&gt;&#xD;&#xA;        &lt;a class=&#34;text-primary-300 dark:text-neutral-700 !no-underline&#34; href=&#34;#what-is-a-network&#34; aria-label=&#34;Anchor&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;/span&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &#xD;&#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;A network is a collection of computers and devices connected together to share resources.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;h2 class=&#34;relative group&#34;&gt;Key Concepts&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;div id=&#34;key-concepts&#34; class=&#34;anchor&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &#xD;&#xA;    &lt;span&#xD;&#xA;        class=&#34;absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 -start-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100 select-none&#34;&gt;&#xD;&#xA;        &lt;a class=&#34;text-primary-300 dark:text-neutral-700 !no-underline&#34; href=&#34;#key-concepts&#34; aria-label=&#34;Anchor&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;/span&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &#xD;&#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;IP Address&lt;/strong&gt; — Unique address for each device&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Switch&lt;/strong&gt; — Connects devices within a LAN&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Router&lt;/strong&gt; — Connects different networks together&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Firewall&lt;/strong&gt; — Protects network from unauthorized access&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;More detailed guides coming soon!&lt;/p&gt;</description>
      
    </item>
    
